Oh, I'll bring them tomorrow, I think.

01:08:48.640 --> 01:08:50.640
Beautiful.

01:08:49.230 --> 01:08:51.230
But it's a real poet at it.

01:08:51.320 --> 01:08:53.320
Real poet.

01:08:53.380 --> 01:08:55.380
Poetry is so great.

01:08:55.480 --> 01:08:58.843
You see, now I'll tell you one thing about poetry.

01:08:58.910 --> 01:09:06.910
In the poetry, poetry means there has to be magic in the word.

01:09:08.080 --> 01:09:13.997
When you say something, it must have a magic.

01:09:16.280 --> 01:09:20.677
If there's no magic, then it's not poetry.

01:09:22.120 --> 01:09:28.120
Then the second thing is that it's precise.

01:09:29.560 --> 01:09:31.560
It has to be precise.

01:09:32.170 --> 01:09:36.170
It has to be small words, sentences.

01:09:36.250 --> 01:09:40.726
Like many propositions and all that are to be dropped out.

01:09:40.780 --> 01:09:44.780
Adjectives to be dropped out, meaning you are allowed.

01:09:46.080 --> 01:09:50.080
So many adverbs can be dropped out.

01:09:50.140 --> 01:09:52.774
But mainly what you can drop out are articles.

01:09:52.830 --> 01:09:54.964
Absolutely.

01:09:57.230 --> 01:10:00.364
Third is that it must have rasa.

01:10:01.200 --> 01:10:03.200
Rasa means the essence.

01:10:03.440 --> 01:10:05.440
It must have the essence.

01:10:05.670 --> 01:10:10.963
And the essence are according to Indian science, are nine tabs.

01:10:11.330 --> 01:10:12.522
Must have any essence.

01:10:12.600 --> 01:10:16.600
Now this is the essence today is of bhakti.

01:10:18.070 --> 01:10:26.780
When you are singing of bhakti and devotion, then you have to use words,

01:10:27.210 --> 01:10:36.470
extremely gentle words, gentle words, beautiful words, words that are delicate,

01:10:37.420 --> 01:10:49.420
the words that express devotion through humility, words of humility.

01:10:49.860 --> 01:10:55.860
Now what I see now with your compositions is that two types.

01:10:56.230 --> 01:11:05.306
One is addressed to others and one addressed to Me.

01:11:05.380 --> 01:11:11.380
In the others you have addressed some to the other people who are not Sahaja Yogis.

01:11:11.390 --> 01:11:19.390
Some your own Sahaja Yogis together and some are addressed to Me.

01:11:19.560 --> 01:11:25.028
So there are three types of compositions you have done.

01:11:25.190 --> 01:11:32.449
Now when you are addressing to others, you need not be that delicate.

01:11:32.530 --> 01:11:38.530
Like what you say, come and see, listen, look up.

01:11:39.630 --> 01:11:42.630
This is what you should do.

01:11:42.860 --> 01:11:45.960
In a gentle way they won't understand.

01:11:46.090 --> 01:11:54.090
So you have to use words which are sort of forcing them, pushing into it.

01:11:54.130 --> 01:11:56.130
What are you doing?

01:11:56.710 --> 01:11:59.710
This is the poem, same way written down.

01:11:59.870 --> 01:12:01.165
And very good poem, no doubt.

01:12:01.240 --> 01:12:07.285
But in this poem, whatever you have written, this one, is good, nice and everything fine.

01:12:07.370 --> 01:12:15.370
But what I find is still a little bit diplomacy.

01:12:15.460 --> 01:12:21.460
Now if you say how many of you want to be saved today, they'll say all of us.

01:12:21.510 --> 01:12:22.510
How do you count?

01:12:22.540 --> 01:12:26.540
How do you find out?

01:12:26.590 --> 01:12:36.590
So the question should be asked in a way in reality, in totality.

01:12:36.610 --> 01:12:43.893
Actually, honestly, put these adjectives in between so that then people understand

01:12:43.920 --> 01:12:48.920
honestly, are we honest?

01:12:49.040 --> 01:12:51.494
But they'll also be, we all want to seek.

01:12:51.530 --> 01:12:55.530
We are all sick as you are sick as you are sick as, why should we run after Mother?

01:12:56.140 --> 01:12:57.140
All right?

01:12:57.260 --> 01:13:09.577
So honestly, and all those things sort of, you see, make it look more objective.

01:13:09.600 --> 01:13:10.600
You fix them.

01:13:10.650 --> 01:13:11.650
You hem them up.

01:13:12.280 --> 01:13:14.280
Otherwise they'll slip out.

01:13:14.360 --> 01:13:20.360
In whatever you're seeing, it should be such that they are pushed into a point, they have

01:13:20.380 --> 01:13:21.782
no escapes left.

01:13:21.820 --> 01:13:27.820
So when you write now, next time, that's a very good poetry, no doubt, but correct it

01:13:28.370 --> 01:13:30.062
when you address to others.

01:13:30.090 --> 01:13:37.090
See that they have no escape.

01:13:37.300 --> 01:13:39.300
That they cannot bhaja.

01:13:39.360 --> 01:13:40.360
All right, Vivaan?

01:13:40.520 --> 01:13:46.823
You are a scholar, so I must ask you permission.

01:13:47.240 --> 01:13:53.240
Now, the second one is when we are singing among ourselves.

01:13:53.660 --> 01:13:58.127
Now, the thing that is joy, joy is a very good one.

01:13:58.210 --> 01:14:02.210
But we are not addressing to folk people.

01:14:02.640 --> 01:14:04.640
That's the point.

01:14:05.240 --> 01:14:08.637
We are addressing to intellectuals.

01:14:08.820 --> 01:14:12.317
So that's a good one between ourselves when we sing.

01:14:12.370 --> 01:14:17.370
We have to address to the intellectuals so we can challenge relatives.

01:14:18.200 --> 01:14:19.797
You say, what have they got?

01:14:19.930 --> 01:14:21.557
With the intellect, what did I get?

01:14:21.660 --> 01:14:23.153
With this, I what did I get?

01:14:23.223 --> 01:14:27.993
All these barren things, useless things, you've found nothing, not a single friend.

01:14:28.060 --> 01:14:32.060
And then come down what I got in search of.

01:14:32.360 --> 01:14:37.360
This relative description should be given.

01:14:37.410 --> 01:14:41.410
So I hope some of you will write poetry on that.

01:14:41.460 --> 01:14:49.455
The third one is what Wakefield has done, is my description and devotion to you.

01:14:49.630 --> 01:14:52.630
Come out, Bhairebaal, I must say.

01:14:53.040 --> 01:14:55.040
I think that's the highest one can do.

01:14:55.720 --> 01:14:56.961
That's the best.

01:14:57.000 --> 01:15:00.000
But still we need all this, we have to have.

01:15:00.030 --> 01:15:02.030
Otherwise we cannot manage.

01:15:02.050 --> 01:15:04.050
So that's a part of it.

01:15:04.120 --> 01:15:22.120
But the essence of it, the praise, where many great poets, many great writers, many great saints and incarnations

01:15:22.160 --> 01:15:26.160
have aspired to sing the praise of the Mother.

01:15:26.200 --> 01:15:29.200
It's a great aspiration.

01:15:29.210 --> 01:15:31.210
Like Markandeya did that.

01:15:31.260 --> 01:15:34.260
Today also we did it after fourteen thousand years.

01:15:34.390 --> 01:15:38.390
Then Adi Shankaracharya did that.

01:15:38.780 --> 01:15:41.766
So poetry of that level should come out.

01:15:41.850 --> 01:15:49.850
I would request you to read those poems, poetry of those people who compose such high class books

01:15:49.920 --> 01:15:53.920
that not a word can be changed, not to be added.

01:15:54.000 --> 01:15:57.000
And that's how you try to perfect it.

01:15:57.560 --> 01:15:58.560
Try to perfect it.

01:15:58.650 --> 01:16:03.650
When you have written it down, sit down, think over it, again try to bring in better words.

01:16:03.750 --> 01:16:05.194
Try to put better words.

01:16:05.210 --> 01:16:09.210
So you actually make it a perfect poetry, a perfect setting.

01:16:09.320 --> 01:16:12.320
That's it.

01:16:12.700 --> 01:16:14.700
But a poet is a poet born poet.

01:16:14.770 --> 01:16:19.145
It's a thing that is born and even after Sahaja Yoga many people suddenly become poets.

01:16:19.220 --> 01:16:24.220
Like Damle never used to, he's an engineer, never is to write but wrote very well.

01:16:24.340 --> 01:16:25.340
Very beautifully.

01:16:25.380 --> 01:16:27.765
Poems are very good even now I think he's very good.

01:16:27.770 --> 01:16:30.770
But there was another fellow, Kade, who did beautiful writing.

01:16:30.920 --> 01:16:34.253
I don't know where are his poems lost but they are somewhere.

01:16:34.280 --> 01:16:38.280
And such tremendous things he has written.

01:16:38.370 --> 01:16:39.370
I was amazed.

01:16:39.470 --> 01:16:43.163
But he said, I don't write, the Saraswati is writing in me.

01:16:43.220 --> 01:16:52.220
So for that you see, the spontaneity is alright but you have to have the technique to write.

01:16:53.110 --> 01:16:56.542
The technique must be there and the spontaneity I'll look after.

01:16:56.580 --> 01:17:00.580
So you have to also develop a little bit of technique how to write it out.

01:17:00.600 --> 01:17:03.600
In these three categories you write of different type.

01:17:03.780 --> 01:17:10.780
So when you write about your mother, you have to be absolutely sure.

01:17:10.800 --> 01:17:19.393
Absolutely one and absolutely surrendered.

01:17:19.510 --> 01:17:28.280
So the whole thing can be an epic, absolutely the top most thing that one can do in poetry

01:17:28.310 --> 01:17:32.080
is to write the praise of the Mother.

01:17:32.150 --> 01:17:33.150
That's the highest.

01:17:33.420 --> 01:17:42.114
So all the poetry is very nice, comes out of very generous heart and also very great hearts.

01:17:42.170 --> 01:17:44.170
But it has to have a technique.

01:17:44.610 --> 01:17:57.610
And the technique is to be little bit understood in a divine way that what makes it a thing

01:17:57.640 --> 01:18:03.640
that throbs in your heart.

01:18:03.900 --> 01:18:10.362
So that you will see yourself that will throb in your heart.

01:18:10.440 --> 01:18:14.440
If you are detached about it you will do it and you will do it very well.

01:18:14.490 --> 01:18:16.490
I was so happy about Chris's.

