01:18:19.370 --> 01:18:22.370
They thought that it is Chris who has done this from Bristol.

01:18:22.400 --> 01:18:26.400
So I said alright let me ask first of all Chris from Bristol.

01:18:27.040 --> 01:18:30.120
Beautiful poetry, beautiful is done.

01:18:30.180 --> 01:18:36.180
Alright, so best of luck to you for all these good poems and poetry that you have done

01:18:36.560 --> 01:18:40.078
and all these pieces are extremely beautiful.

01:18:40.090 --> 01:18:50.090
But we have to perfect it, make it better and better and in tune with divine vibrations.

01:18:50.498 --> 01:18:53.724
So you should say vibrations also.

01:18:53.780 --> 01:18:56.424
What gives you the best vibrations?

01:18:56.500 --> 01:19:02.154
Tunes could be simple, could be complicated, could be magical, could be anything.

01:19:02.280 --> 01:19:15.280
But the poetry must not narrate but create magic.

01:19:15.950 --> 01:19:25.112
Sanskrit really says when it is there is a magic, the light of the magic.

01:19:25.420 --> 01:19:29.954
When there is a light of the magic then you should call it the poetry.

01:19:31.630 --> 01:19:34.304
When there is a rasa then there is kave, there is poetry.

01:19:34.400 --> 01:19:40.988
Otherwise no, without rasa there is no.

01:19:41.310 --> 01:19:44.548
Now this is the part where the composer is concerned.

01:19:44.600 --> 01:19:52.600
Now for the part of the ones who have to sing, to sing from your heart.

01:19:52.750 --> 01:19:56.318
Knowing before whom you are singing, from your heart.

01:19:56.350 --> 01:20:01.350
You are not singing for yourself, you are singing for me, singing for the whole universe.

01:20:01.540 --> 01:20:09.824
Say it from your heart knowing that I am before you, understanding that.

01:20:09.990 --> 01:20:14.990
Secondly you must have the technique of singing it, it is very important.

01:20:15.790 --> 01:20:24.174
All these techniques are built in through tradition by understanding whatever is not proper is thrown away.

01:20:25.240 --> 01:20:30.240
It should not be that one line close, long, another line comes short, long.

01:20:30.590 --> 01:20:34.590
There should be a proper technique about it, how to do it.

01:20:34.820 --> 01:20:38.820
See like a free verse business is no good for Sahaja Yoga.

01:20:39.020 --> 01:20:44.020
So that technique you have to know how to sing it with that the music.

01:20:44.050 --> 01:20:52.380
But the drum is an essential part of every music because that is the part where Anahata is placed.

01:20:52.470 --> 01:20:55.470
So in sound drum has to be there.

01:20:55.510 --> 01:20:59.510
When you are singing there has to be drum as well as other accompaniments.

01:20:59.850 --> 01:21:05.850
Any accompaniments you have but drum is an essential part that has to be there.

01:21:05.870 --> 01:21:10.870
And the whole thing should be on a rhythmic understanding that you see,

01:21:10.890 --> 01:21:14.298
you have seen how Indians have a rhythmic understanding you see.

01:21:14.350 --> 01:21:19.350
They cut it into three halves, four halves, they bring it back and how they cut it, how they go off beat.

01:21:19.640 --> 01:21:27.640
It's really too much but you can compose to a great extent on those lines.

01:21:28.050 --> 01:21:36.050
And that technique has to come properly understood.

01:21:36.190 --> 01:21:42.297
